# Conclusion

This report provides a short, rubric-aligned analysis of the Adult ASD screening dataset. We (1) described the prevalence of `ASD_traits`, (2) compared screening score distributions by outcome group using tables and a boxplot, and (3) fit a logistic regression model to quantify the association between screening score and ASD traits after adjusting for age and sex. Future work could extend the model by adding additional covariates (e.g., ethnicity, family history, jaundice) and evaluating predictive performance (e.g., ROC/AUC).
